# Goal Description
The objective is to implement **Phase 7 (API Bridge)** and **Phase 8 (React Dashboard)** for the Mini OS Kernel Simulator, as outlined in the system architecture.

We will:
1. Embed the lightweight **Crow** C++ web framework into the simulation engine to provide REST endpoints and a WebSocket state broadcaster.
2. Build a **React + TypeScript** frontend using Vite, styled dynamically to resemble a modern **Windows 11 interface** (using glassmorphism, a taskbar, and draggable/dockable windows for each OS module panel).
3. Connect the frontend to the C++ engine so the simulation logic runs entirely in C++, while the frontend provides a rich, interactive "OS" view.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> - Integrating **Crow** requires modifications to the CMake setup (fetching dependencies via `FetchContent`).
> - The UI will use **TailwindCSS** to rapidly build the Windows aesthetic. Please confirm you are okay with Tailwind.
> - The integration will completely replace the current CLI loop in `main.cpp` with a long-running web server.

## Proposed Changes

---

### Layer 2 — API Bridge (C++ Engine)

We will modify the engine to host a local HTTP and WebSocket server using Crow.

#### [MODIFY] [engine/CMakeLists.txt](file:///e:/Semester%204/OS-CEP/OS-Kernel-Learning-Simulation/os-simulator/engine/CMakeLists.txt)
- Uncomment and implement `FetchContent` for `Crow` and `nlohmann_json`.
- Add `bridge_lib` target.

#### [NEW] [engine/bridge/RestServer.h](file:///e:/Semester%204/OS-CEP/OS-Kernel-Learning-Simulation/os-simulator/engine/bridge/RestServer.h)
- Declare `class RestServer` that encapsulates a `crow::SimpleApp`.
- Declares endpoints for controlling the `SimulationState` (start, step, mode, quantum, policies, load workload).

#### [NEW] [engine/bridge/RestServer.cpp](file:///e:/Semester%204/OS-CEP/OS-Kernel-Learning-Simulation/os-simulator/engine/bridge/RestServer.cpp)
- Implements the 12 REST routes mapped to `/sim/...`, `/process/...`, `/scheduler/...`, etc.
- Serializes `SimulationState` via `nlohmann/json`.

#### [NEW] [engine/bridge/WsServer.h](file:///e:/Semester%204/OS-CEP/OS-Kernel-Learning-Simulation/os-simulator/engine/bridge/WsServer.h)
- Implements WebSocket routes via Crow. Subscribes to the `EventBus` for `TICK_ADVANCED` events to broadcast the entire simulated state to connected UI clients.

#### [MODIFY] [engine/main.cpp](file:///e:/Semester%204/OS-CEP/OS-Kernel-Learning-Simulation/os-simulator/engine/main.cpp)
- Remove the step/auto console demo.
- Instantiate `RestServer` and start the Crow application loop on port 8080 (REST) and 8081 (WS, or multiplexed on 8080 if using Crow WS).

---

### Layer 3 — React Dashboard (Windows Interface)

We will create a Vite + React + TS project inside the `dashboard/` directory.

#### [NEW] [dashboard/package.json](file:///e:/Semester%204/OS-CEP/OS-Kernel-Learning-Simulation/os-simulator/dashboard/package.json)
- Bootstrap with `npx create-vite@latest dashboard --template react-ts`.
- Add dependencies: `tailwindcss`, `lucide-react`, `recharts`, and optionally a drag-and-drop library (e.g., `react-rnd`) for moving windows.

#### [NEW] [dashboard/src/App.tsx](file:///e:/Semester%204/OS-CEP/OS-Kernel-Learning-Simulation/os-simulator/dashboard/src/App.tsx)
- Sets up the global Windows desktop background.
- Mounts the taskbar (`SimControlBar`) at the bottom.
- Manages an array of currently open "Windows" (Process, Memory, Scheduler, Sync, Decision Log).

#### [NEW] [dashboard/src/hooks/useSimState.ts](file:///e:/Semester%204/OS-CEP/OS-Kernel-Learning-Simulation/os-simulator/dashboard/src/hooks/useSimState.ts)
- Connects to `ws://localhost:8080/ws` and returns the global state JSON, forcing a single re-render per tick.

#### [NEW] [dashboard/src/components/Taskbar.tsx](file:///e:/Semester%204/OS-CEP/OS-Kernel-Learning-Simulation/os-simulator/dashboard/src/components/Taskbar.tsx)
- Replaces standard `SimControlBar`. Looks like Windows Taskbar. Shows time, start menu, and icons corresponding to internal engine panels. Contains start/pause/step controls.

#### [NEW] [dashboard/src/components/DesktopWindow.tsx](file:///e:/Semester%204/OS-CEP/OS-Kernel-Learning-Simulation/os-simulator/dashboard/src/components/DesktopWindow.tsx)
- Reusable component providing Windows 11 glass UI, title bar, minimize, maximize, and close buttons wrapper around panels.

*Other Component Panels will follow the requirements outlined in the SDD (ProcessPanel, SchedulerPanel, etc.), rendered cleanly using Windows UI design systems (Mica material, fluent icons).*

## Open Questions
- There's a comment regarding `websocketpp` in the SDD, but `Crow` recently supports WebSockets out-of-the-box natively. Using Crow for BOTH REST and WS on a single port (e.g. 8080) is substantially easier and reduces dependency bloat. Are you perfectly fine with using Crow's built-in WebSockets rather than bringing in `websocketpp`?
- Should we use `Tailwind CSS` for styling the Windows UI dashboard? The guidelines mention avoiding Tailwind unless requested, but here you requested a specific complex styling (Windows UX) and it is standard for Vite/React web apps. Let me know if you prefer plain Vanilla CSS instead!

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Once C++ REST integration is done, we will execute direct `curl` or `Invoke-RestMethod` commands against `http://localhost:8080/sim/step` to ensure engine advances logic correctly.

### Manual Verification
- We will boot up the Vite server natively via `npm run dev` and test the connection against the running C++ executable to verify state streams into the UI properly.
